NAME
  size - check the size of a file in bytes

SYNOPSIS
  size FILE
  size FILE -a

DESCRIPTION
  The size program allows checking the size of a file. This is useful for checking whether or not a file can fit onto a floppy or other storage medium.

OPTIONS
  -a
	Shows the actual byte value of a file, instead of resolving to kilobytes (or megabytes, if applicable)
  
EXAMPLES
  size init.lua
	Will output the file size of init.lua
	
  size /lib/filesystem.lua -a
	Will output the file size for filesystem.lua in bytes, even though filesystem.lua is over 1kb.